div1.p: Territory of Washington, Third Judicial District. ss. To J. C. Mitchell

In the name of the United States of America, You are herby commanded to be and appear at the District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, at Seattle, for the District aforesaid, at 1 o'clock in the after noon of the 3rd day of October A. D. 1889 then and there to give everidence in a certain cause thering pending, wherein

In the matter of the application Plaintiff and of Geo W Anderson for writ of Habeas Corpus Defendant and to remain in attendance on said Court from day to day therafter until discharged, and herin fail not at your peril. Witness on behalf

Witness, the HON C H Hanford Richard A. Jones, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said District Court, this 3rd day of October 1889 R M Hopkins Clerk. By H T Harmon Deputy.
No. 7264 In the District Court, holding terms at Seattle, Washington Terr. SUBPOENA.

Territory of Washington, Counrt of King ss. I herreby certify that I recieved the within Subpoena on the 3 day of October A. D. 1889 and personally served the same on the within named by the reading the same to each of them, in King County, Washintgon Territory, on the 3 day of October A. D. 1889 Dated King County, W. T., 3 day of October A. D. 1889 B Brockevery Bailiff
FEES. Serving Subpoena, - - $1.10 Mileage, 2 miles, $.20 cer 6.0 $ 1.10
